can bananas be frozen to use in a shakes or something they get brown so fast in the summer yes of course you don't even have to peel them just put them in a plastic container and freeze if you are making a smoothie then don't even bother defrosting just stick them straight in the blender or you can bake with them instead but you will have to defrost then if you do that put the bananas in a bowl as they get a bit slimey perfectly alright for baking though or take a fresh banana cut it in half and insert a popsicle stick then dip in melted chocolate and freeze really good enjoy Ice cream Milkshake Domesticated turkey Banana Tofu Bread McDonald's Casting In-N-Out Burger Cuisine of Denmark Bagel Coffee Breakfast Maple syrup Cleveland Browns Spidey Super Stories Toilet humour Potato Cold Stone Creamery Dim sum French fries Cookware and bakeware Yoplait Cha chaan teng Japanese cuisine Cuisine of the Philippines Barbecue Pottery Bong Customs and etiquette of Japan Lindy Basic New York Giants Ceramics Skateboarding trick Hamster Jewish cuisine Austin Powers Rum Textile manufacturing Internal ballistics Rice pudding Hot dog Treehouse of Horror V Chocolate Balboa Island, Newport Beach, California Twinkie Glacier Chocolate Salty Balls Minor Harry Potter Beasts Futurama (TV series - season 1) Phil Hendrie Rod Stewart Soldering Chicken Cookie Water (molecule) Ice Puff pastry Sherbet Baking Vermicompost Pencil Cheesecake M&M's Pizza Brewery She Loves You Table saw Chopsticks Futurama (TV series - season 4) Drill bit Have I Got News For You Cuisine of Brazil The Daily Show Melt-Banana Refrigerator Daiquiri Sea ice Economy of Colombia Mammoth The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time weapons and items Sandwich Cryonics Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 Billiards Homer Simpson Welding Korean cuisine Mango Nestl__ Fish and chips Hamburger Printed circuit board Tea Plastic Poi (food) Bacon Fast-food restaurant Sour cream 